## 📊 EXECUTIVE SUMMARY

### What This Animation Does
This is a **scroll-triggered staggered entry animation** where content panels slide in from the right while fading in, one after another, as the user scrolls down the page.

### Key Characteristics
| Aspect | Description |
|--------|-------------|
| **Trigger** | Scroll (IntersectionObserver) |
| **Animation Type** | Slide + Fade |
| **Start State** | translateX: 80px, opacity: 0 |
| **End State** | translateX: 0px, opacity: 1 |
| **Duration** | ~3 seconds |
| **Easing** | Cubic-bezier ease-out |
| **Stagger** | ~100ms between panels |
| **Panel Count** | 11 panels (1 always visible + 10 animated) |
| **Hover Effects** | ❌ **NONE** on panels (pointer-events: none) |

### Important Discovery
**There is NO hover effect on the panels.** The panels have `pointer-events: none`, meaning they cannot be hovered or clicked. The "movement" you see when moving your mouse is actually the scroll-triggered animation being activated by mouse-induced scrolling.

