## 📝 IMPLEMENTATION NOTES

### 1. Font Loading
The animation uses "PP Neue Montreal" fonts. You'll need to:
- Purchase/obtain the font license
- Load them via @font-face or Google Fonts
- The font has multiple weights: Hairline, Extralight, Thin, Light, Book, Regular, Medium, Semibold, Bold, Extrabold, Black

```css
@font-face {
  font-family: 'PP Neue Montreal Hairline';
  src: url('fonts/PPNeueMontreal-Hairline.woff2') format('woff2');
  font-weight: 100;
  font-style: normal;
}
/* ... add all weights */
```

### 2. No Hover Effects
**Important:** The panels have `pointer-events: none`. This means:
- No hover effects on panels
- No click interactions on panels
- Only text links inside panels are interactive

### 3. Browser Support
The animation uses:
- CSS `transform` and `opacity` (supported everywhere)
- CSS `transition` (supported everywhere)
- IntersectionObserver API (supported in modern browsers)
- CSS Grid (supported in modern browsers)

### 4. Performance Tips
```css
/* Use will-change for smoother animations */
.panel-content {
  will-change: transform, opacity;
}

/* Use hardware-accelerated properties */
transform: translateX(80px); /* Good */
/* Avoid: */
left: 80px; /* Bad - causes repaint */
```

